message.content: Case report of a 45-year-old male COVID-19 patient with hypertension and diabetes mellitus.
A 65-year-old male with a history of hypertension and diabetes presented with fever and cough, and was diagnosed with COVID-19.
A 45-year-old male COVID-19 patient presented with acute respiratory distress syndrome and was successfully treated with extracorporeal membrane oxygenation (ECMO) therapy.
A 45-year-old male COVID-19 patient with comorbidities presented with bilateral pneumonia and acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS) requiring mechanical ventilation.
